      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONSTANTINA (1) led as favourite in a higher-graded race last start at Penrith and while she couldn't see it out she stuck on for a 2.2m third. Led from wider when winning over this distance the last time she raced here last month so can take advantage of the ace draw. SPIRIT KING (3) was solid when midfield at Menangle last start and will relish the return to this circuit having put together a string of wins and placings prior. Should get his chance from a favourable draw. WALTER WARLOCK (9) has been tackling stronger races so will enjoy the class drop. Draws for a trail and can be dangerous if he gets the gaps. THE CID (4) showed pleasing improvement last time out when he came from the outside barrier to finish runner-up at this venue. Go well again from the lower draw.",
